<br>
While it may make actually *taking* a shot at the AoW more difficult, it would be bad form to spawn and waste the AoW, as such, wiping to a mob that is partially comparable to the AoW would be a good indicator that you are going to lose the AoW and thus, delay his kill by a full week. <br>
<br>
It then, therefore, makes sense to ensure that the guild has at least a better-than-average chance. If *nothing else* the guild should co-ordinate with the guild currently up for the AoW: if they kill the idol and then wipe on the AoW, the guild up in the rotation should be able to kill the AoW so that it isn't wasted. <br>
<br>
We've come into the issue of delaying spawns before, I would ask that those reading this thread realize that the single biggest negative outcome of a raid is to have the mob poof, with no loot and no one else able to kill it. Even if a raid fails against a mob that others can kill, at least someone else would make use of it. <br>
<br>
I would support, and do support, a criteria as suggested here; either fight and kill the idol unslowed, or have the guild up for rotation all present and accounted for when the AoW spawns so that a failed attempt does not mean that the loot poofs as well. <br>
<br>
Either one seems like it would work, long and short term. <br>
<br>
Yers,<br>
